							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script, partially punctuated, and Ashkenazi square script, partially punctuated.  	<name type="person" role="scribe">Yitsḥaḳ ben Ovadiah ben Daṿid of Forli</name> (Gaio di Servadio), active in Florence 1441-1470, inscribed in the colophon of volume 2, Add MS 19945, folio169v. Decorated by <name type="person" role="artist">Zanobi Strozzi</name>.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						
